Container.Note:
This phase is a transient phase so that we can retrieve the saved username from local storage on the device. Traditionally this sort of thing would be done in the index.html or index-hybrid.html and any values from local storage or cookies passed into the edgeConnects datastore.

 

The interesting thing with Hybrid model is that the index-hybrid html which is used as the entry point to edgeConnect is stored locally in the device and as it turns out exists in a different domain to the local storage edgeConnect webapplication has access to. Hence we have to introduce this transient phase to getLocalStorage for the username. Once initialised in the Webview, this phase reads the value from local storage and immediately resubmits the form via the forward button.
